cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.CY 

This paper proposes a framework for learning accurate cognitive models in ill-structured domains using neural networks. The paper focuses on the application of this framework in adaptive online tutoring systems, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of neural networks for cognitive model discovery and skill difficulty estimation falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the application of the framework in natural language processing tasks such as Chinese character recognition and article selection, which falls under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
